# The Elden Beast · the living incarnation of the Ring

The Elden Beast is the living incarnation of the Elden Ring — a vast golden creature sent down by the Greater Will from the void beyond the sky. It did not merely carry the Ring or guard it; it became the Ring, and it dwells within the Erdtree, within Radagon.

It is the final adversary of the game. To mend or remake the Elden Ring, the Tarnished must slay the god-beast that IS the Ring — the Order itself given flesh, struck down so that it may be reforged. It fights as it exists: a star-born leviathan swimming in a sea of gold.

Its emergence is ethereal because it belongs wholly to the unseen — sent by the Greater Will, descended from the void beyond the sky. It is not a warrior of the land but the Order made animal and eternal, dwelling in a golden body.
